e friends with the Queen was good too. She bit her lip and thought for a second. She had really wanted to go see her horse, make sure everything was okay with him, but then she also wanted to watch the two that were riding in. Her dark hair waved into her sunbronzed face for a moment as the breeze blew around her, but she ignored it and walked on to the horses...figuring she'd see the two later~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uempressxena142.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EmpressXena142</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#993300>(4/16/02 3:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ausxip.com/graphics/Xena/X44.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good.</span><hr size=1> :looks to Baily:<br>
